    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nhttps://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?id=297950\r\nNVIM v0.10.1\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/po/zh_CN.UTF-8.po\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/po/zh_TW.UTF-8.po\r\n\r\nThis will cause the neovim interface not to be Chinese when Chinese users set “LANGUAGE” to “LANGUAGE=zh_CN:en_US”. （https://wiki.archlinux.org//title/Localization/Simplified_Chinese#User-specific_locales）\r\nI don't think translations should have “UTF-8” in the file name.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nexport LANGUAGE=zh_CN:en_US\r\nnvim\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nSet LANGUAGE=zh_CN:en_US and neovim will use Chinese.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\narchlinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nxfce4-terminal\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nArch repo ",
